examples.en: The crew narrowly avoided shipwreck.
They successfully avoided each other for days.
He avoided the draft because of a foot injury.
Alan narrowly avoided an accident.
She avoided his long searching look.
Peter had always thought of Kate as someone to be avoided.
They avoided what could have been an ugly situation.
Both pilots took evasive action and a collision was avoided.
In her speech, she carefully avoided any mention of her costar.
She avoided reporters at the airport by merging into the crowds.
The soldier avoided military duty by shooting off one of his toes.
It was noticeable that many of them avoided answering the question.
She carefully avoided his eyes (=did not look directly at his face).
These fish are quite tolerant as long as extremes of pH are avoided.
The Prime Minister narrowly avoided a leadership challenge last year.
The recession could be avoided if business keeps a firm grip on its costs.
Reviewers have nibbled at phrases, but have avoided the principal questions.
...unfortunately, some local bullyboys had made the park their turf, and families avoided it...
She consciously avoided walking past the abandoned house, with its broken windows and sagging porch.
She avoided answering our questions directly, instead reiterating that the answers could be found in her book.
He has not concealed his hard-line views, but has avoided coming into direct public confrontation with the party leadership.
